Petrobras Needs $17 Billion in New Financing, Reuters Says

-- B y   J u a n   P a b l o   S p i n e t t o
-- 
2011-02-18T16:30:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/petrobras-needs-17-billion-in-new-financing-reuters-says.html
  Petroleo Brasileiro SA ,  Brazil ’s
state-controlled oil company, will need $17 billion in “new
money” through 2014, Reuters said, citing Chief Financial
Officer  Almir Barbassa .  Petrobras, as the Rio de Janeiro-based company is known,
may consider tapping Brazil’s national development bank, known
as BNDES, and the Norwegian sovereign wealth fund for the
financing, the executive said, according to Reuters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Juan Pablo Spinetto in London at 
 jspinetto@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts in Buenos Aires at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  